<div id="stitle" style="display:none;">Notebook Entry</div>
<dl id="n09162e"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n09" href="#n09162e">N09 (VI.B.1)</a>:  <a href="../../ff/fnbs/n09all.htm#n09162e"> 162(e)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> fighting G / (climate)</blockquote> <dd class="well"> <blockquote class="sources">Watch how these ugly old blacks will neither temporise nor tamper with the idea of God being over all in His own world: even the word &ldquo;climate&rdquo; he avoids, and in its place will substitute the Creator&apos;s name. Even a Missionary bravely battling against African climate is told by his pot-black brother that he is <mark>&ldquo;fighting God&rdquo; (i.e. climate)</mark>. <small> Dan Crawford, <a name="BTLG1" href="../../ff/fdra/fdex.htm#BTLG1"><cite title="source">Back to the Long Grass</cite></a> (1923) 201</small></blockquote> </dd></dl>
